agent2: I already changed save()'s signature to add dry_run (now multi-line with '*,' making format/dry_run keyword-only after fp,format). New signature:
def save(self, fp: StrOrBytesPath | IO[bytes], format: str | None = None, *, dry_run: bool = False, **params: Any) -> None:
Also edited the body: added 'if dry_run: fp = io.BytesIO()' before the existing 'elif open_fp:' block (~line 2561), and guarded the two fp.close() calls with 'and not dry_run'. I did NOT touch the self._ensure_mutable() line (~2544) - that's still untouched, so your edit there should apply cleanly. When adding preserve_readonly, please just append it as another keyword-only param after dry_run in the signature I already changed, rather than rewriting the whole def line, to avoid clobbering my dry_run addition.
